snippet.title: Cats all the rage for April Fools' Day jokes
snippet.description: Both Google and Opera reveal cat-themed April Fools' Day jokes, with the former offering a QWERTY keyboard for felines and the latter showing off a cat-friendly browser.

snippet.title: Yo, 'Game of Thrones' raps: Official hip-hop mix tape coming
snippet.description: "Game of Thrones" is about to get down with the release of a free mix tape of rap, hip-hop, and Latin artists laying down tracks for the realm.

snippet.title: Mama mia! Physics-themed 'Bohemian Rhapsody' rocks
snippet.description: A physics graduate student uses his scientific knowledge, and his pipes, to create an incredible a capella cover of Queen's "Bohemian Rhapsody."

snippet.title: Securus eZoom tracking and safety locator
snippet.description: The Securus eZoom tracking and safetly locator's hardware is quite good, but expensive operation costs and buggy software tarnishes its recommendation.

snippet.title: The Internship should have Googled some jokes
snippet.description: The Wedding Crashers are back -- and this time they're crashing The Big Bang Theory in Google-backed comedy The Internship.

snippet.title: Yo! Bum rush the torrent, with a boost from Public Enemy
snippet.description: Longtime P2P fan Chuck D and Public Enemy give fans a new song and offer a remix contest, delivered via BitTorrent's new Bundle technology.

snippet.title: In new S4 ad, Samsung replaces iPhone jokes with a fart joke
snippet.description: Samsung decides that for its latest Galaxy S4 ad, it's best to charm with babies and their noises and not bother with comparative humor.

snippet.title: Dongle jokes and a tweet lead to firings, threats, DDoS attacks
snippet.description: A developer tweets her objection to jokes told at a conference, leading to the dismissal of one of the men -- and herself as well.

snippet.title: Apple's new iPad ads: No Samsung jokes (well, maybe one)
snippet.description: Apple releases two new iPad ads that largely offer a continuation of the perception that Apple is the only tablet game in town.
